Diagnosis (emended from
Siddiqi 2000
): Belonolaiminae . Small to medium-sized ( 0.5–1.5 mm ), arcuate to curved when relaxed. Lateral field usually bearing 6 incisures in lateral view, occasionally 4 or 10–12 incisures. Body cuticle formed into blocks by longitudinal striae or grooves. Cephalic region offset, with six radial grooves, with 6–7 annuli, and moderate sclerotization; labial disc inconspicuous, four-lobed. Median bulb near middle of oesophagus or more anterior. Vulva in a cavity or depression, with epiptygma. Vagina vera sub-square in lateral view. Female tail conoid to subcylindrical with rounded or pointed tip; terminal tail cuticle abnormally thickened, may or may not be annulated; spicules slender; gubernaculum crescent-shaped in lateral view.
